# =============================================================================
# PLACEHOLDER - HSBC Trust Store (CA Certificate Bundle)
# =============================================================================
# This file must contain the HSBC CA certificate bundle in PEM format.
# It is used in the Dockerfile:
#   COPY hsbc-truststore.pem /etc/ssl/certs/hsbc-truststore.pem
#   pip.conf cert=/etc/ssl/certs/hsbc-truststore.pem
#
# The actual trust store (~2956 lines, ~174 KB) contains multiple CA
# certificates with "Bag Attributes" metadata (PKCS#12 export format).
# Obtain the real file from the FAB-734 branch or the HSBC infrastructure team.
#
# Expected structure (repeated for each CA certificate):
#   Bag Attributes
#       friendlyName: <certificate alias>
#   -----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
#   <Base64-encoded certificate data>
#   -----END CERTIFICATE-----
#
# Replace this entire file before building the container.
# pip install will fail without valid CA certificates.
# =============================================================================
Bag Attributes
    friendlyName: PLACEHOLDER-HSBC-ROOT-CA
-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
PLACEHOLDER_REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_HSBC_TRUSTSTORE_CERTIFICATES
This is not a valid certificate. Replace this entire file with the real
hsbc-truststore.pem from the FAB-734 branch or HSBC certificate distribution.
-----END CERTIFICATE-----
